.TH "nilfs_ioctl_delete_checkpoint" 9 "nilfs_ioctl_delete_checkpoint" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nilfs_ioctl_delete_checkpoint \- remove checkpoint
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nilfs_ioctl_delete_checkpoint
.BI "(struct inode *inode "  ","
.BI "struct file *filp "  ","
.BI "unsigned int cmd "  ","
.BI "void __user *argp "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "inode" 12
inode object
.IP "filp" 12
file object
.IP "cmd" 12
ioctl's request code
.IP "argp" 12
pointer on argument from userspace
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
\fBnilfs_ioctl_delete_checkpoint\fP function removes
checkpoint from NILFS2 file system. This ioctl is used in rmcp
utility.

Return Value: On success, 0 is returned and a checkpoint is
removed. On error, one of the following negative error codes
is returned.

-EPERM - Operation not permitted.

-EFAULT - Failure during checkpoint removing.
